Wait - re-examining: the closures do `keysRef.current.w = true` using the ref object. `keysRef` is the stable `useRef` wrapper. So even though `.current` is replaced, future key events will write into the new object. And `tick` also reads from `keysRef.current`, so it will read from the same new object. This is correct.

